{"url": "https://www.echoandrig.com/about", "title": "About Echo & Rig \u2014 Echo & Rig | Las Vegas & California Steakhouse", "viewport": "width=device-width, initial-scale=1", "charset": "utf-8", "h3": "Discover Echo & Rig\u2019s origin story, meet Chef Sam Marvin & the ER team@@Echo & Rig believes you deserve value & quality - always. We are your neighborhood steakhouse and butcher shop always offering culinary experiences with best-in-class steaks & ingredients and without unaffordable prices. @@Echo & Rig\u2019s origin story is a true mix of femininity and masculinity.   @@  \u2726 Echo: the nymph who masterfully distracted the queen for Zeus though was ultimately caught and made to only repeat.  \u2726 Rig: the power of mankind. While this is an abstract story, we interpret it through a beautiful pairing of our cuts of steaks that we source from our purpose-driven farming partners from around the world - such as Cape Grim in Tasmania and Creek Stone in Kansas.   @@Guests will always enjoy a selection of cuts, of finishes and of entrees. From classic butcher cuts to more selective, we know how to cut them and it\u2019s the top two and a half percent of all beef graded by the USDA. We want to always give your option & show you that there are different ways to eat a steak.@@Chef Sam Marvin is the Owner and Executive Chef of Echo & Rig Steakhouse in Las Vegas, Henderson and Sacramento. @@A California native with serious classical French training, Chef Sam earned his cooking stripes working in top-rated Michelin star restaurants. He previously owned and operated Bottega Louie in Downtown Los Angeles, before branching out with his own brands in Las Vegas and Sacramento. @@His Las Vegas Echo & Rig restaurant was named LV Weekly\u2019s \u201c2021 Best Las Vegas Steakhouse.\u201d Chef Sam competed in Food Network\u2019s cooking competition, Beat Bobby Flay, and earned a prestigious win.@@Our restaurants are designed for our guests. We endeavor to create incredible and memorable experiences each time you dine with us or visit our butcher shop. From the quality of our food, the level of guest experiences from our staff and the overall design and energy of our interiors, Echo & Rig\u2019s ethos is woven into every step. @@In addition to our steakhouse, Echo & Rig proudly houses a butcher shop, full of high-quality cuts available directly to our guests to take home and enjoy. @@Chef Sam Marvin has travelled the world to visit ranches and farms, meeting with the teams who are raising the best cattle. Our butcher shop serves a range of cuts, including limited edition beef from Cape Grim and Robbins Island, Tasmania, home to the \u201ccleanest air in the world\u201d.@@Butcher Shop Locations:@@LOCATIONS@@ABOUT US@@BUTCHER SHOP@@THE GOODS@@GROUP EVENTS@@REVIEW ", "h4": "Las Vegas@@Sacramento@@Henderson@@Our Story@@Chef Sam Marvin@@Careers @@About@@Gallery@@Features@@Collaborations@@Shop Gift Cards  @@Newsletter Sign Up@@Book Las Vegas  \u21f2@@Book Sacramento \u21f2@@Book Henderson \u21f2@@ Las Vegas@@Sacramento@@Henderson@@Privacy Policy       Terms of Use      Site Credits      The Goat LLC \u00a9 2023", "canonical": "https://www.echoandrig.com/about", "og:site_name": "Echo & Rig | Las Vegas & California Steakhouse", "og:title": "About Echo & Rig \u2014 Echo & Rig | Las Vegas & California Steakhouse", "og:url": "https://www.echoandrig.com/about", "og:type": "website", "twitter:title": "About Echo & Rig \u2014 Echo & Rig | Las Vegas & California Steakhouse", "twitter:url": "https://www.echoandrig.com/about", "twitter:card": "summary", "jsonld_url": "https://www.echoandrig.com", "jsonld_name": "Echo & Rig | Las Vegas & California Steakhouse", "jsonld_description": "", "jsonld_image": "//images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/62ccca18424c3120f98944aa/dda56506-2094-4154-9d0f-810e4eb7b2ee/Echo+and+Rig+Steakhouse+and+Butcher+Shop+logo+1.png", "jsonld_@context": "http://schema.org", "jsonld_@type": "WebSite", "jsonld_1_legalName": "440 S. Rampa